CatDescriptText: Mrs. Virginia Benton, housewife, 814 Fourth Avenue was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 10, 1959, pg. A1, with question: "How do you think Soviet Premier Khrushchev's visit to the United States affected relations between our country and Russia? Were you or were you not impressed by his visit to Pittsburgh?" Answer reads: "People now seem to be impressed that perhaps Khrushchev is sincere."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Virginia Benton wearing flecked suit with wide collar, and earrings, holding large envelope, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
